This paper deals with deep learning for face swapping detection, which is a computer vision problem, making cs.CV the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves subjective assessment by human subjects, which could fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). The use of deep learning for detecting malicious uses of images could also fall under the sub-category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves uncertainty estimation, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
